The paper deals with the cooperative spectrum sharing between multiple primary and secondary users, which involves the allocation of resources and the negotiation of prices. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of communication networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT) to model and analyze the spectrum sharing problem. The paper also discusses the security and privacy issues (cs.CR) that arise due to the incomplete information of the secondary users. Finally, the paper proposes a matching-based approach to solve the spectrum sharing problem, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
